@title all functions related to creating kittens

@dev Creates a new gen0 kitty with the given genes and
  creates an auction for it.

@dev Computes the next gen0 auction starting price, given
  the average of the past 5 prices + 50%.

params._to: The address to be granted transfer approval. Pass address(0) to  clear all approvals.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Kitty that can be transferred if this call succeeds.

params._addr: The address that will be able to sire with your Kitty. Set to  address(0) to clear all siring approvals for this Kitty.
params._sireId: A Kitty that you own that _addr will now be able to sire with.

bidOnSiringAuction(uint256,uint256).details: Completes a siring auction by bidding.  Immediately breeds the winning matron with the sire on auction.

params._matronId: - ID of the matron owned by the bidder.
params._sireId: - ID of the sire on auction.

params._matronId: The ID of the Kitty acting as matron (will end up pregnant if successful)
params._sireId: The ID of the Kitty acting as sire (will begin its siring cooldown if successful)

params._matronId: The ID of the proposed matron.
params._sireId: The ID of the proposed sire.

createGen0Auction(uint256).details: Creates a new gen0 kitty with the given genes and  creates an auction for it.

createPromoKitty(uint256,address).details: we can create promo kittens, up to a limit. Only callable by COO

params._genes: the encoded genes of the kitten to be created, any value is accepted
params._owner: the future owner of the created kittens. Default to contract COO

createSaleAuction(uint256,uint256,uint25.details: Put a kitty up for auction.  Does some ownership trickery to create auctions in one tx.

createSiringAuction(uint256,uint256,uint.details: Put a kitty up for auction to be sire.  Performs checks to ensure the kitty can be sired, then  delegates to reverse auction.

giveBirth(uint256).details: Looks at a given Kitty and, if pregnant and if the gestation period has passed,  combines the genes of the two parents to create a new kitten. The new Kitty is assigned  to the current owner of the matron. Upon successful completion, both the matron and the  new kitten will be ready to breed again. Note that anyone can call this function (if they  are willing to pay the gas!), but the new kitten always goes to the mother's owner.

params._matronId: A Kitty ready to give birth.

returns._0: The Kitty ID of the new kitten.

isPregnant(uint256).details: Checks whether a kitty is currently pregnant.

params._kittyId: reference the id of the kitten, any user can inquire about it
reference the id of the kitten, any user can inquire about it

pause().details: Called by any "C-level" role to pause the contract. Used only when  a bug or exploit is detected and we need to limit damage.

setAutoBirthFee(uint256).details: Updates the minimum payment required for calling giveBirthAuto(). Can only  be called by the COO address. (This fee is used to offset the gas cost incurred  by the autobirth daemon).

setCEO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the CEO. Only available to the current CEO.

params._newCEO: The address of the new CEO

setCFO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the CFO. Only available to the current CEO.

params._newCFO: The address of the new CFO

setCOO(address).details: Assigns a new address to act as the COO. Only available to the current CEO.

params._newCOO: The address of the new COO

setGeneScienceAddress(address).details: Update the address of the genetic contract, can only be called by the CEO.

params._address: An address of a GeneScience contract instance to be used from this point forward.

setMetadataAddress(address).details: Set the address of the sibling contract that tracks metadata.  CEO only.

setSaleAuctionAddress(address).details: Sets the reference to the sale auction.

setSiringAuctionAddress(address).details: Sets the reference to the siring auction.

params._tokenId: The ID number of the Kitty whose metadata should be returned.

tokensOfOwner(address).details: This method MUST NEVER be called by smart contract code. First, it's fairly  expensive (it walks the entire Kitty array looking for cats belonging to owner),  but it also returns a dynamic array, which is only supported for web3 calls, and  not contract-to-contract calls.

params._owner: The owner whose Kitties we are interested in.

params._to: The address of the recipient, can be a user or contract.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Kitty to transfer.

params._from: The address that owns the Kitty to be transfered.
params._to: The address that should take ownership of the Kitty. Can be any address,  including the caller.
params._tokenId: The ID of the Kitty to be transferred.

unpause().details: Unpauses the smart contract. Can only be called by the CEO, since  one reason we may pause the contract is when CFO or COO accounts are  compromised.

withdrawAuctionBalances().details: Transfers the balance of the sale auction contract to the KittyCore contract. We use two-step withdrawal to prevent two transfer calls in the auction bid function.

devdoc.title: all functions related to creating kittens

approve(address,uint256).notice: Grant another address the right to transfer a specific Kitty via  transferFrom(). This is the preferred flow for transfering NFTs to contracts.

approveSiring(address,uint256).notice: Grants approval to another user to sire with one of your Kitties.

autoBirthFee().notice: The minimum payment required to use breedWithAuto(). This fee goes towards  the gas cost paid by whatever calls giveBirth(), and can be dynamically updated by  the COO role as the gas price changes.

balanceOf(address).notice: Returns the number of Kitties owned by a specific address.

breedWithAuto(uint256,uint256).notice: Breed a Kitty you own (as matron) with a sire that you own, or for which you  have previously been given Siring approval. Will either make your cat pregnant, or will  fail entirely. Requires a pre-payment of the fee given out to the first caller of giveBirth()

canBreedWith(uint256,uint256).notice: Checks to see if two cats can breed together, including checks for  ownership and siring approvals. Does NOT check that both cats are ready for  breeding (i.e. breedWith could still fail until the cooldowns are finished).

erc721Metadata().notice: Name and symbol of the non fungible token, as defined in ERC721.

giveBirth(uint256).notice: Have a pregnant Kitty give birth!

isReadyToBreed(uint256).notice: Checks that a given kitten is able to breed (i.e. it is not pregnant or  in the middle of a siring cooldown).

ownerOf(uint256).notice: Returns the address currently assigned ownership of a given Kitty.

supportsInterface(bytes4).notice: Introspection interface as per ERC-165 (https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/165).  Returns true for any standardized interfaces implemented by this contract. We implement  ERC-165 (obviously!) and ERC-721.

tokenMetadata(uint256,string).notice: Returns a URI pointing to a metadata package for this token conforming to  ERC-721 (https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/721)

tokensOfOwner(address).notice: Returns a list of all Kitty IDs assigned to an address.

totalSupply().notice: Returns the total number of Kitties currently in existence.

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfers a Kitty to another address. If transferring to a smart  contract be VERY CAREFUL to ensure that it is aware of ERC-721 (or  CryptoKitties specifically) or your Kitty may be lost forever. Seriously.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfer a Kitty owned by another address, for which the calling address  has previously been granted transfer approval by the owner.

unpause().notice: This is public rather than external so it can be called by  derived contracts.
